MobiGo by VTech ($60 for children from 3 to 8) is the cheapest and most user-friendly solution, equipped with a qwerty keyboard. However, the games included on it aren't as educational as those on the Leapster Explorer ($70, for kids ages 3 to 12), which comes with a new, brighter screen after Leapfrog's first major overhaul of the Leapster series.
