In order not to have to do without this tradition, many employees pay for it out of their own pocket.
Whatever the situation, the lowest prices are being demanded, confirms the chairman of the Barcelona Restaurants Board, Gaietà Farràs.
The representative of the umbrella organization does not yet dare to predict what the holidays will look like this month.
"People think twice before making a reservation."
"They want to go out, but they pay close attention to prices," he points out.
Business will go well with those "who offer quality at good prices with a good service," he adds, reminding us that customers save in times of crisis, which is why prices around 25 euros are the most in demand.
A survey in various centrally located restaurants shows that the evening of December 17 leads the providers to collapse.
