"To be in possession of our thoughts and reality, we must nuance: and nuance often means putting your finger in the wound and harassing those who feel much more comfortable thinking in the form of caricatures, in black and white, in ready-made ideas without nuances, and also to harass the powerful who prefer,  He noticed dividing the world into black and white and invited us to rediscover the meaning of writing.
