Finally, they cast a harsh light on the way in which the French Presidency has tried to manipulate the media in order to make them believe the idea that Syrian President Bachar al-Assad played a central role in the liberation of Clotilde Reiss.
In truth, he had done nothing in this regard.
A diplomatic telegram issued in Paris on August 12, 2009, is entitled "Iran: French comments on the way hostage-taking is handled."
