"Do this all the more, especially since the Iranians ask you not to do this."
Because "silence solves nothing", over the discussion attempts over in an inconspicuous way, the Iranians are "masters in evasive maneuvers".
Mr. Richier adds that the arrest of foreigners is a "common Iranian tactic": "hostage-taking for the purpose of political blackmail."
He announces that the release of Clotilde Reiss from prison (which should take place on August 16, the day she takes refuge in the French embassy) "requires the payment of a large sum of money to the Iranians" (230,000 euros bail).
And he says that the Elysée anticipates further hostage-taking, a phenomenon that "will intensify."
The Iranians could "arrest another of the approximately 1,800 French citizens living in Iran in the near future," he said.
28 August 2009.
